abstract: >-
  NexusRAG is a fully local retrieval-augmented generation system for
  scientific papers, built around an honest, reproducible benchmark. It
  fuses dense (BGE-small) and sparse (BM25) retrieval with reciprocal-rank
  fusion and a confidence-gated corrective re-retrieval, and answers with
  a local model and inline citations. The accompanying CPU-only study on
  SciFact and NFCorpus measures each component (bootstrap confidence
  intervals, paired randomization tests, Holm correction) and evaluates
  faithfulness as evidence detection (ROC-AUC, PR-AUC) against lexical and
  cross-encoder baselines.
